# Privacy Policy : 

Privacy Policy for PayFlow
Last Updated: 26.08.2024
Type

At PayFlow, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.

1. Information We Collect
Email, Username, and Password:

Email/Username: We only collect your email address, which serves as your username for identification purposes within the app. We do not use your email for any other purpose, such as marketing or sharing with third parties.
Password: We collect your password solely for account access. Your password is encrypted using industry-standard encryption methods (bcrypt) to ensure it remains secure. We do not store your password in plain text.
2. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used exclusively for the following purposes:

Account Identification: Your email/username is used to identify you when you log into the app.
Authentication: Your password is used to authenticate your identity and provide secure access to your account.
We do not use your information for any other purposes, and we do not share your information with third parties.

3. Data Security
We take data security seriously and have implemented measures to protect your information:

Password Encryption: As mentioned, your password is encrypted using bcrypt, an industry-standard encryption algorithm.
No Plain Text Storage: We do not store your password in plain text, and it cannot be accessed by anyone, including our team.
4. Data Collection
We do not collect, store, or process any personal information beyond your email/username and encrypted password. We do not track your activities or gather additional data from your device.

5. Third-Party Sharing
We do not share your information with any third parties. Your data remains private and secure within the PayFlow app. Your information is stored on a database. 

6. Your Rights
Access and Deletion: You have the right to access the information we store about you and request its deletion at any time. If you would like to delete your account, please contact us at the email provided below.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:

Email: support@payflowapp.com

By using PayFlow, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. We may update this policy from time to time, and we will notify you of any significant changes.



For any questions or support, contact us at : rawima2@gmail.com

